<a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85408">Wubao's Gear</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urobert135.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robert135</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/6/02 2:49:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11731.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: huh?</span><hr size=1> His point in saiying the +2hps dmg is very obvious, either you were being sarcastic or really don't know what he is talking about. <br>
<br>
 a 2 dmg weapon does 5 hps dmg most of the time, You know this.<br>
<br>
the disease does not only add 2 disease dmg, which as a 2 dmg spell it would do exactly 2 dmg. it is added as a sort of melee damage. so it has the same modifier as a 2 * 2  mod like all other melee, however it does not have an inate AC check, it has a disease resistance check. Against SSra, or other HIGH AC mobs this would be much more benificial.<br>
<br>
The point is lets say a mob has crappy DIS resists, but high AC. You hit the mob w a 12/20 melee only weapon but you get 50% dmg taken off because of mob AC. Your dmg is now (12*2)/2  + 1 = ~ 13 dmg. Where as with the disease weapon you would do (10*2)/2 +1 + 4 = ~ 15 dmg.<br>
<br>
His points are valid and worth parsing. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urobert135.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robert135</A> at: 10/6/02 2:53:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskewert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skewert</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/6/02 2:50:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11731.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: huh?</span><hr size=1> A 12/20 straight up weapon has it's damage CHECKED EACH HIT too.  It's check is just based on the mobs AC and your ATK, not solely the mobs Disease Resistance.<br>
<br>
I believe the +2 disease dmg works this way.<br>
<br>
Think of a 0(zero) damage, 20 dly weapon, with +12 disease damage, on a mob with zero AC and zero disease resistance.  This weapon should then perform identically to a conventional 12 dmg, 20 dly weapon, and the max damage of each weapon would be the same.<br>
<br>
I'm saying the +2 disease damage on the hammer is calculated as if it were melee damage, using your STR, ATK, and weapon skill to determine how much damage that +2 disease damage actually does.  The benefit of this, is that it ignores the mobs AC, and only looks at the mobs disease resistance.<br>
<br>
